I'd rather these be protists than worms.
附加记录：    

I agree that these would be better as something other than worms, but I heavily dislike the term . They're not consistently considered a valid way of grouping organisms. A link.

It is mildly intriguing how a group of worms could replicate the organ systems, but that's not enough to carry the article and I sincerely doubt that it was intended to. In my opinion, these could be amoebas (still , but a legitimate genus that just doesn't fit into a pre-existing kingdom). Given the large amounts of, er, biomass that passes through any given plumbing system, 840 could probably construct a full digestive system, operated manually by the colony.

Alternatively, they could go man-o-war style and say  and be organs, looking like the pipes just one day grew a digestive system for the hell of it, which is what I think you're going for here.

And it would just make my day if a plumber stuck his arm down the drain to see what was up and the drain ate his arm.








