I think something more akin to a bird's craw, where large indigestible objects (rocks, for instance) are used to crush matter until it fits better and is more easily digestible. So, for instance, your spelunker suddenly gets pulled in by peristalsis, and by the time his companions can recover him, he's had several bones broken and a few square feet of skin dissolved by the acidic mucus (which, incidentally, would need to be washed off, so one hopes there's a stream nearby or our poor spelunker is in for a world of hurt).

OTOH, not everything the Foundation contains is scary, and this is weird enough to qualify for SCP status, IMO.





